featured_reviews.review_id: A couple of months back I wrote an issue about My mum's funeral.  I would like to let every one (the public) know that the issue has been solved by the concerned committee of the Tawa Islamic Centre (Zirus Zuber, Moveen, Don and Mustapha).  I am very happy with the outcome of their findings and have no further concerns.  We are still going to the Tawa Islamic Centre as usual.  If anyone is still carrying my previous complains and has an issue with this please contact the committee members of the center who are the best people to explain the outcome of their findings.  If we are happy and have no issues with the center I don't expect the public to have any concerns or questions against the center.  I sincerely thank the committee members to come forward to deal with my issues and they have dealt with the issue with great dignity.

I got a chance to Offer Juma at Porirua Islamic Center second time in my life, it is always blessing to pray juma here. Qari shb drliver Friday sermon in Urdu/Hindi, English and Arabic languages for understanding and learning about Islam. What a lovely place to worship here. The worship place for Muslims, brotherhood, love, peace, care and harmony all under one roof.
If you are worried or sad come see the Qari/Molana Abdul Jabbar shb to take his guidance. He is lovely human being.
